  "articleSummary": "Framed as a reflective “lessons learned” journey, this article details the author’s migration of an aging Gatsby blog to a modern, performance-optimized stack centered on Astro. The core thesis argues that static site generators should prioritize build-time efficiency, framework neutrality, and minimal client-side JavaScript, positioning Astro as the ideal solution for content-heavy sites. Key technologies evaluated and deployed include MDX, Tailwind CSS, ShadcnUI, Pagefind, Utterances, and Netlify, alongside a technical comparison of Astro’s server-rendered components versus traditional client-side frameworks. Written in a practical, tutorial-style tone, the piece targets front-end developers and technical bloggers seeking actionable guidance for modernizing legacy static sites.",
